get.description:
Generate a `robots.txt` or `ai.txt` file that blocks AI crawlers from scraping your content without a license. Covers 16 known AI bots including GPTBot, ClaudeBot, Googlebot-Extended, PerplexityBot, and more.

**Why this matters:** Most AI crawlers respect `robots.txt`. By serving this file, you signal that your content is behind Opedd's licensing system — and provide a path for compliant access via the agent purchase flow.

**How to use it — step by step:**

1. Find your Publisher ID in your Opedd dashboard under Settings
2. Fetch the policy from this endpoint
3. Serve it at `yourdomain.com/robots.txt` (or append it to your existing one)

```bash
# Fetch and save as robots.txt
curl "https://api.opedd.com/ai-defense-policy?publisher_id=YOUR_ID" \
  > robots.txt
```

For Next.js or similar, you can return it dynamically:

```js
// pages/robots.txt.js or app/robots.ts
export async function GET() {
  const res = await fetch(
    `https://api.opedd.com/ai-defense-policy?publisher_id=${process.env.OPEDD_PUBLISHER_ID}`
  )
  const text = await res.text()
  return new Response(text, { headers: { 'Content-Type': 'text/plain' } })
}
```
